Hi,

I am trying to crawl websites through Umbra / RabbitMQ to get more URLs 
generated by JS.
I set up everything as it is described here: 
https://sbforge.org/display/NAS/Integrating+Umbra+And+Heritrix+3

I can see in my crawl logs that the URLs are beeing sent to 
Umbra/RabbitMQ because of the Status *sentToAMQP*****
I think this means that so far my Requests are successfully sent .....I 
can see the requests in the RabbitMQ Webadmin as well.

The problem is that I can not see anything comming back from 
Umbra/RabbitMQ ..... the documentation says that I should see URLs with 
the status*received* *FromAMQP***. This doesnt happen but instead I get 
this in my job logs:

*SEVERE problem starting AMQP consumer (will try again after 30 seconds) 
(in thread &#39;AMQPUrlReceiver-starter-restarter&#39;)*

My logfile from rabbitmq says this:

=INFO REPORT==== 6-Jul-2015::12:24:41 ===
accepting AMQP connection &lt;0.15717.1733&gt; (127.0.0.1:45721 -&gt; 127.0.0.1:5672)

=INFO REPORT==== 6-Jul-2015::12:24:45 ===
accepting AMQP connection &lt;0.15762.1733&gt; (127.0.0.1:45724 -&gt; 127.0.0.1:5672)

=INFO REPORT==== 6-Jul-2015::12:25:21 ===
closing AMQP connection &lt;0.15762.1733&gt; (127.0.0.1:45724 -&gt; 127.0.0.1:5672)

=INFO REPORT==== 6-Jul-2015::12:25:21 ===
closing AMQP connection &lt;0.15717.1733&gt; (127.0.0.1:45721 -&gt; 127.0.0.1:5672)


As you can see rabbitmq is acception 2 connections from heritrix and 
when I finish the crawl both are closed.
I think they are used to send the URLs. After acception the connections 
and some seconds the &quot;AMQP consumer&quot; problem occours and keeps comming 
every 30 seconds as the AMQPUrlReceiver tries to start a consumer.

Does anyone have an idea what might be the problem? Did I miss anything 
which wasn&#39;t described in the howto above?


Thanks,
Markus



